The paper deals with the problem of finding a multicut in a graph, which is a well-studied problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve graph algorithms, parameterized complexity, and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
